docs.snippet: European Union foreign ministers met on Sunday to discuss potential ramifications of Mr. Trump’s win. Many of his statements have left some European nations vulnerable.

headline.print_headline: European Leaders, Reeling, Meet to Weigh Fallout of U.S. Election

docs.abstract: European Union foreign ministers hold emergency meeting to discuss uncertainty over election of Donald J Trump as future president of America in regards to his stance on major global accords that range from NATO to landmark environmental legislation; representatives from Great Britain, France and Hungary are not in attendance.

docs.snippet: Clashes over costs and fears that security measures would chase away customers hobbled Yahoo’s efforts, leading to the 2014 breach of 500 million users.

headline.print_headline: Hacker Threat Took Back Seat at Yahoo, Insiders Say
headline.main: Defending Against Hackers Took a Back Seat at Yahoo, Insiders Say

docs.abstract: Insiders say clashes over financial priorities and security measures that fell short led to 2014 hacking attack that stole credentials of 500 million Yahoo customers; breach, undetected until now, is latest black eye for chief executive Marissa Mayer.
